    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-11-03T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-11-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="645"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">365.115 D 58/81: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-03T12:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1924—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>218. Department’s 182, October 27, 6 p.m. Delegate at Angora on November 2nd made
                    representations as instructed in above-mentioned telegram and reports as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“November 2, 3 p.m. Discussed at length this morning with Tewfik Kiamil
                                Bey<note n="35" xml:id="d645fn35">Turkish Under Secretary of State
                                for Foreign Affairs.</note> property transfer question, using
                            arguments outlined in High Commission’s 86, October 30, 3 p.m. He stated
                            the Turkish Government considers protocol of 1874<note n="36"
                                xml:id="d645fn36">Malloy, <hi rend="italic">Treaties</hi>,
                                1776–1909, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 1344.</note> and
                            Ottoman law of 1873 [<hi rend="italic">1867?</hi>]<note n="37"
                                xml:id="d645fn37">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 1346.</note> as null and void and
                            right to acquire real property therefore non-existent until coming into
                            effect of Turkish-American treaty. I replied that my Government did not
                            accept this point of view and I urged him to examine the question in a
                            practical way with a view to avoiding an issue. He undertook to do this
                            but he holds out little if any hope of satisfactory adjustment.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
